>There has also long been the suspicion that some NSA cryptosystems
>have keys with sufficient internal structure that it is statistically
>unlikely to choose a strong key, and that most keys chosen without
>knowing the algorithm are weak.

NSA as much as admitted that this is how the CCEP works.  They give you
a choice between choosing weak keys yourself or getting strong keys from
them.  Of course there is always the third alternative: not to use CCEP.
Which would you choose?

